# ============================================================================
# ModCord Bot Configuration
# ============================================================================
# Copy this file to .env and fill in the required values below.
# IMPORTANT: The .env file should NEVER be committed to version control.
#            Add .env to your .gitignore file.
# ============================================================================

# PostgreSQL Database Password
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Required: Yes
# Type: String (alphanumeric recommended, avoid special chars that need escaping)
# Description: Password for the PostgreSQL database user (typically 'postgres')
# Example: POSTGRES_DB_PASSWORD=my$ecureP@ssw0rd123
# Security: Use a strong, randomly generated password (min 16 characters)
POSTGRES_DB_PASSWORD=your_secure_database_password_here

# Discord Bot Token
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Required: Yes
# Type: String (alphanumeric + special characters)
# Description: Authentication token for your Discord bot application
# How to get it:
#   1. Go to https://discord.com/developers/applications
#   2. Select or create your application
#   3. Navigate to "Bot" section
#   4. Click "Reset Token" to generate a new token
#   5. Copy the token (DO NOT share this with anyone)
# Security: Treat this like a password. If exposed, regenerate immediately.
# Example: DISCORD_BOT_TOKEN=MjM4MDk0OTUyMzI5MzA1MjE2.CvVSmw.abcdef123XyZ
DISCORD_BOT_TOKEN=your_discord_bot_token_here

# OpenAI API Key
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Required: No (only if using AI/LLM features)
# Type: String (starts with 'sk-')
# Description: API key for OpenAI or OpenAI-compatible API (e.g., LocalAI, Ollama)
# How to get it:
#   - OpenAI: https://platform.openai.com/api-keys
#   - LocalAI: Use your self-hosted instance URL instead
#   - Ollama: Typically http://localhost:11434 (no key needed)
# Alternative APIs:
#   - LocalAI (self-hosted): Set OPENAI_API_KEY=http://localhost:8080
#   - Ollama (local LLM): Set OPENAI_API_KEY=http://localhost:11434
# Security: Keep this private. Rotate regularly if exposed.
# Example: OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-proj-abc123XyZ...
OPENAI_API_KEY=your_openai_api_key

# ============================================================================
# Setup Instructions
# ============================================================================
# 1. Copy this file:     cp .env.example .env
# 2. Edit .env with your values (use a text editor, NOT git)
# 3. Verify .gitignore includes: .env
# 4. Run the bot:        ./run.sh
#
# ⚠️  SECURITY CHECKLIST:
#   1 .env is in .gitignore
#   2 Never commit .env to git
#   3 Use strong, unique passwords
#   4 Rotate tokens if exposed
#   5 Only share .env.example (template), never .env (with secrets)
# ============================================================================